  "text": "In this work, we solve the radial Schrödinger equation by using the three-point difference central method from central (r = 0) towards outside (r → ∞) point by point. The details of this method can be found in Ref. [CITATION_1] . To overcome the singular behavior of 1/r 3 in the spin-dependent potentials, following the method of our previous work [CITATION_2] , we introduce a cutoff distance r c in the calculation. Within a small range r ∈ (0, r c ), we let 1/r 3 = 1/r 3 c . It is found that the masses of the 3 P 0 states are sensitive to the cutoff distance r c , which is easily determined by the mass of χ c0 (1P).",
